## Acceptance
- [ ] package.json gains a "start" script that runs `node src/server.js`, PRESERVING the pre-existing "test"/"typecheck"/"lint" scripts (merge, do not clobber); the server reads its listen port from process.env.PORT (default 3000).
- [ ] The SQLite store file path is configurable via DB_PATH (default ./data/app.db); the parent directory is created at startup if absent, so data is written on-disk and survives a restart.
- [ ] POST /auth/register with a new non-empty {username,password} returns 201 and a JSON body {id, username}.
- [ ] POST /auth/register with a missing or empty username or password returns 400 with a JSON body whose only field is a string "error".
- [ ] POST /auth/register with an already-taken username returns 409 with a single-field {error} JSON body.
- [ ] POST /auth/login with correct credentials returns 200 and a JSON body {token} usable as Authorization: Bearer <token>.
- [ ] POST /auth/login with an unknown username or a wrong password returns 401 with a single-field {error} JSON body.
- [ ] The bearer-token guard (requireAuth) accepts a token signed with the server secret and rejects a missing, malformed, or tampered token — exercised directly in test/auth.test.js (the end-to-end 401 on a protected route is pinned by the projects-and-tasks Story that owns those routes).
- [ ] Stored user passwords are scrypt-hashed with a per-user salt — no plaintext password is written to the store.

## Verify
- node --test test/auth.test.js (contract)
- node --check src/server.js (validate)

